================================================================================
    brita
================================================================================

a backlight adjuster for Linux

Brita is small console program that can be used for dimming and brightening
a screen of your laptop.

I've written this program because my Chromebook doesn't like "xbacklight" method,
so brita modifies files present in sysfs. It *likely* works on other laptops and
it shouldn't be able to do any damage, but it is FLOSS - absolutely zero warranty,
but I'll be very glad if YOU make it better ;-)

================================================================================
    Build
================================================================================

    ./make
    ./brita.py --help
  OR
    python3 setup.py install
    brita --help

================================================================================
    Usage
================================================================================

  Setting the brightness to certain value:
    brita 800
  Setting the brightness to certain percentage of the maximum:
    brita 60%
  Brightening the screen:
    brita +500
    brita +30%
  Dimming the screen:
    brita -400
    brita -30%
